        <h2><b>Greetings</b></h2>
        <p>Welcome to Amnesty PLUS. We appreciate your engagement with global issues that are
            happening around the world and look forward to building stronger connections among
            community members. Our overarching goal is to write to spread awareness around the world and
            try to stop global injustices through the activities of everyone involved.
            Please read the instructions/guidelines below and refer to them when writing, and
            communicating with your peers and leadership. It will be expected that you abide by these
            guidelines during your entire participation in Amnesty PLUS. Infractions will be treated
                according to the consequences section below.</p>
        <hr>
        <h2><b>General Rules</b></h2>
        <p>
            ● Be respectful of everyone you interact with.<br>
            ● Use formal language when communicating and writing.<br>
            ● Strictly follow the social media guidelines when you are participating through such mediums.<br>
            ● Be collaborative and supportive of your peers.<br>
            ● All members are expected to meet deadlines.<br>
        </p>
        <hr>
        <h2><b>Consequences</b></h2>
        <p>
            ● A failure to meet any deadlines will result in a strike. If a member receives 3 strikes, they
            will be expelled from the organization. These strikes will reset yearly.<br>
            ● If a member demonstrates any abuse, profanity, or inappropriate/negative behavior, they
            will receive a warning from the leadership team with repeat offenses resulting in
            expulsion from the organization.<br>
            <br>
            If you have any other questions, comments, concerns, etc; feel free to contact our leadership
            team at this email address: headquarters@amnestyplus.org
        </p>
